 remarkably fresh, nuanced, and worldly conceptions of freedom thriving amidst the archived everyday. The Brink of Freedom's speculative, "idian globalities ultimately ask us to improvise radical ways of living in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aAfrican AmericansxColonizationzLiberiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aLiberia - History - 10th century. 0aMayaszMexicozYucatán (State)xHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Africa / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374107zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374107.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles